   "source": [
    "# Attention Mechanism Visualization\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook provides interactive visualizations of the attention mechanism in transformer models.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Table of Contents\n",
    "1. [Scaled Dot-Product Attention](#scaled-dot-product-attention)\n",
    "2. [Multi-Head Attention](#multi-head-attention)\n",
    "3. [Attention Pattern Visualization](#attention-pattern-visualization)\n",
    "4. [Real-world Examples](#real-world-examples)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "from matplotlib.patches import Rectangle\n",
    "import warnings\n",
    "warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Set style\n",
    "plt.style.use('seaborn-v0_8-whitegrid')\n",
    "sns.set_palette(\"husl\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"✅ Dependencies loaded successfully!\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Scaled Dot-Product Attention\n",
    "\n",
    "The core attention computation can be expressed as:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\\text{Attention}(Q, K, V) = \\text{softmax}\\left(\\frac{QK^T}{\\sqrt{d_k}}\\right)V$$\n",
    "\n",
    "Let's implement this step by step with visualization:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Create sample matrices for demonstration\n",
    "seq_len, d_k, d_v = 8, 16, 16\n",
    "np.random.seed(42)\n",
    "Q = np.random.randn(seq_len, d_k)\n",
    "K = np.random.randn(seq_len, d_k)\n",
    "V = np.random.randn(seq_len, d_v)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Query shape: {Q.shape}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Key shape: {K.shape}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Value shape: {V.shape}\")"
   ]
  }
 ],
